<subSubSection id="C32660E89E019F11FF0DFA9F10E71EA4" pageId="14" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8333639E019F11FF0DFA9F10E71EA4" blockId="14.[151,1437,829,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="B948EF719E019F11FF0DFA9F13771E7F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1333,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4E929E019F11FD5DFA9F114E1E7F" author="Li" box="[663,770,1333,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="365" refString="Li, Z. Z. (1990) Four new species of the genus Scaphoideus (Homoptera: Euscelidae). Acta Zootaxonomia Sinica, 15 (4), 464 - 470. [in Chinese with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1990">Li (1990)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingRegion id="49F8FD819E019F11FC8FFA9F11D31E7F" box="[837,927,1333,1358]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
based on seven male specimens. It externally resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C48E09E019F11FEC4FAF310041E40" box="[270,584,1369,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B948EF719E019F11FEC4FAF310041E40" box="[270,584,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">Scaphoideus albomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be readily distinguished by the narrowed connective processes and aedeagus with a pair of apical lateral processes.
</paragraph>
